<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-15-0693 </DOCNO><TEXT>The lecture shows how different energy projects may be compared and evaluatesthe usefulness of the projects in money based on costs of the alternatives.The presented method may be used for all energy projects at all levelsin the energy system including measures for reducing the consumer consumption.If the energy tariffs picture the macro-economic costs for developingnew power, the use of this method helps to promote and stimulate a rationalenergy consumption in the society. The consumer is always interestedin meeting his demands for useful energy as reasonable as possible. Bychoosing an energy carrier composition which reduces the energy coststo a minimum and reducing energy loss by energy conservation measures,this may be obtained. 1 table, 7 drawings.</TEXT></DOC>